The Duchess of Cambridge is dressed in a long khaki summer dress, as is Princess Charlotte.
Prince William, the Duke of Cambridge, is wearing shorts and a collared shirt, just like Princes George and Louis.
It is not clear who took the photograph or when it was taken.
Last year the royal family posed for their Christmas card photograph on a stack of straw in front of a pile of logs at their country home in Norfolk.
The heir to the throne, Prince Charles, and his wife Camilla also released a picture to serve as a Christmas greeting.
Photographer Sam Hussein caught him at the races in Ascot in June.
Charles, who has a cap on his head and a mask on his face, helps Camille put her mask on, which matches her light-colored dress.
According to efotbal.cz, Slavia has promised Berbr a million for the title, but Tvrdík denied it.
Prague - The investigators in the current corruption case are said to be working on the assumption that the accused former vice-president of the Czech Football Association, Roman Berbr, was promised one million Czech crowns by Prague Slavia for the league title in the 2018/19 season.
The website efotbal.cz reported this, stating that it had access to part of the police records.
The chairman of the board of the Vršovice club, Jaroslav Tvrdík, stated that the red and whites had not committed any corruption.
The website published transcripts of police wiretaps, in which the former sporting director of Slavia, Jan Nezmar, who left the championship club last summer, is the main figure.
The former influential official of the red-and-whites was, according to the file, in frequent contact with both Berbr and the former sports director of the then second-league Vyšehrad, Roman Rogoz, who is also among the accused in the case.
The police were reportedly working with information that Slavia had promised Berbatov a financial reward for winning the title.
In 2019, the SK Slavia Praha team won the first league title.
The police authority had the knowledge that Roman (Berbr) was promised a million-dollar bribe by the officials of SK Slavia Praha for winning the league, the server quoted from the file.
According to the criminalists, the following day Berbr met not only with Nezmar, but also with the chairman of the board of Slavia, Tvrdík.
According to the server, it is not clear from the report whether the police is still dealing with this information.
Tvrdík denied any corruption.
Between 2015 and 2017, we actively tried to change the situation in Czech football and we offered an alternative for its development.
We have never committed an illegal act, we have not tried to influence referees in breach of the fair play rules, and we have not paid any financial compensation to anyone in this regard," said Tvrdík for Seznam Zprávy.
In the recordings, Nezmar, among other things, indiscriminately insults some former dark-skinned players of Slavia, and also slanders his former boss, Tvrdík.
The case of alleged match-fixing through referees was sparked by a police raid in mid-October last year at several locations, including the headquarters of the Czech Football Association in Prague.
Berbr is the highest-ranking person involved in the affair and is no longer involved in football.
In mid-January, he was released from custody, just like former Vyšehrad Sports Director Rogoz.
Helicopters, tanks, and BVPs are the LARP of the Cold War.
The new tanks will be of a fundamentally worse type (the gunners will have to leave the armoured cabin and carry the ammunition by hand without protection).
The cars - Toyota Hi-luxes - are new and good
Trucks and various armoured vehicles - at a decent level, moreover, it is already possible to get rid of the Praga V3S even in specialised units.
Aircraft: combat - decent but at the end of its lease, transport - too small with a short range, but modern.
Drones - few and only small types with no combat potential
Rockets - we don't have any (but we manufacture them and export them abroad)
NGOs: Cold War-era, outdated; short-range: good, modern, relatively good number.
I have a story.
I have a hunting lodge right next to the city.
The nutria were coming out of the river and causing damage to the crops, so I sat there.
When I arrived, I could see that there was a fisherman on the other side of the river.
I didn't want to make a scene, so I sat down and the guy probably didn't notice me.
I hoped that he would leave before anything came out, but of course, the fox left after a while.
I let her get to 40 yards before I decided to shoot.
The poor fisherman almost had a heart attack, he was waving his flashlight in all directions, so I called out to him that it was a fox.
When I got off the saddle, I was black and blue.
In other words, a man can be a loser.
On the other hand, it's not a war. It would take a lot of coincidences for something to happen. You would probably be seen on a thermal camera, which almost everyone has today.
So in a visible place, put your expensive things next to your feet in your sleeping bag and you should be fine.
