They tend to be less open and do not share their opinions openly.
On the other hand, Eastern Europeans, and especially we Czechs, are used to talking "as if a beak had grown on our nose".
See, you'll do a survey where you ask people if they like Muslims.
In the Czech Republic, most people will tell you that they don't.
In the West, they will tell you how much they like migration, how everyone should help them, and how we Czechs are racist scum.
And then they go and vote for parties like the AfD.
They fear cancel culture, saying this publicly means losing your job and being lynched by the media.
