Identical due to rotation of units, so the soldiers don't have to relearn where things are, all the buildings are exactly the same.
One of them is the Atom Museum of the Brdy, and the other two are abandoned.
It's funny that the USSR didn't want to have nuclear warheads on its own territory, either for security reasons or because of the speed of deployment due to its more western location.
In the underground bunkers (there are two in each maple tree), only the warheads were stored, not the entire missiles, as it is said.
If it was necessary to use this weapon, a special unit came to pick up the head and mount it on some kind of carrier.
In addition to the museum maple, the rest are in a dilapidated state.
In second grade of primary school we had a Gypsy classmate, and we spent 4 years with him.
He was pretty good, he made some good jokes, he was often a bit over the top, but he was like our mascot.
Everyone played with him, he often went and wanted to explain something, he was almost always there, he played sports with us, he didn't steal snacks or phones, he was dressed neatly.
He went to nature schools, did all sorts of monkey business, but he was fine, he never got into any trouble.
In 8th or 9th grade, the siblings enrolled in the same grade, but in different classes.
Shortly thereafter, they beat up the teacher, the police were often called there, they threatened and intimidated other students...
I sometimes sell things online (old stuff, things I don't need, etc.) and I've often sold things to Gypsies, they always had money, they didn't try to haggle with me over the price, and the communication was calm.
I've even sold a car this way, the guy called a month later to say he had already transferred it to himself...
I say myself that I'm not a racist; it doesn't matter to me whether someone is white, black, yellow, blue or something else, as long as they act as they should in a decent society (work, function, don't beat up women, just normal behaviour).
But as soon as someone comes, they stretch out their hand, they evict people from their flats and houses, there's just a mess around them, they cause trouble... it doesn't matter what colour they are, but it will bother me.
I have no problem with African migrants, as long as they participate here, start a business, work, learn the language (not necessarily, at least English), and respect our culture.
If they believe in Allah, I don't care, as long as they respect my traditions and culture, I will respect theirs.
