The man from Hrob "shot" his girlfriend from Kostomlat
The man from Hrob unwittingly helped the officers to secure his nationally wanted girlfriend from Kostomlat, who was the subject of an arrest warrant.
He summoned her himself.
However, he did so in an indirect way.
He first approached a passer-by and invented a story that he had been robbed.
After being called to the scene, officers were astonished when the alleged "robber" told them he had made the whole thing up to get them to come to the scene.
In fact, he just wanted to ask the guards how to file a report with the Czech Police.
After checking the identity of the man and his girlfriend, the officers discovered that the woman was on the list of wanted persons, in a nationwide search, and an arrest warrant had been issued for her.
The case is therefore being handled by the Czech Police.
