The Bethlehem flame is in the Czech Republic, the scouts received it from Austria
Břeclav - The flame lit in Bethlehem, where according to the Christian tradition Jesus Christ was born, is in the Czech Republic.
However, the scouts did not drive to Vienna this time because of the coronavirus pandemic. In the morning, they received him from their Austrian colleagues at the Reintal - Břeclav border crossing.
They received it at the border last year as well.
The Bethlehem light is a beautiful Christmas tradition that we participate in as a troop every year and I look forward to it very much.
It is an honour for me to be chosen, said scout Amálie Budíková to the present journalists.
While last year the handover took place at the Mikulov-Drasenhofen border crossing, directly on the border bridge, now at the Reintal-Břeclav border crossing in the car park.
The scouts usually take the train to Vienna for him.
The distribution of the flame across the Czech Republic is not changing.
The scouts traditionally set off with the Bethlehem light by train first to Brno, where they will hand it over to the diocesan bishop Vojtěch Cikrle.
On Saturday, 18 December, scout couriers will take care of the subsequent distribution of light, travelling in selected express and passenger trains.
From them, the light will be taken over by local scouts or volunteers, who will then continue to spread the flame throughout the Czech Republic, even to places where there are no railways.
This year too, scouts must comply with the current measures to prevent the spread of the coronavirus.
It is going the same way as last year.
We recommend that both the delivery teams and the organisers of local events wear masks of course, try to keep their distance, keep their numbers to a minimum, refrain from singing together, in short, act in a way that is as safe as possible, described the spokesperson of the Bethlehem Light event, Zuzana Hrbková.
The tradition of the Bethlehem light travelling across Europe was born in 1986 in Austria.
The goal is to spread the idea of peace, friendship and harmony along with the flame.
The Bethlehem light is a symbol for believers of hope, a light that overcomes the darkness.
In the Czech Republic, the scouts and scouts have been taking care of its propagation for more than 30 years.
The action is supported by hundreds of volunteers, the flame is therefore also a symbol of altruism and human solidarity.
All the news, including a list of places where people can go to get a flame, can be found on the website www.betlemskesvetlo.cz.
