From a legal perspective, covid is on the list of infectious diseases.
That is to say, in the same group as HIV, the plague, yellow fever or typhoid.
§ 152 Dissemination of an infectious human disease
(1) Any person who willfully causes or increases the risk of the introduction or spread of an infectious disease among humans shall be punished by imprisonment for up to six months, by a fine, or by confiscation of property.
(2) The offender will be sentenced to imprisonment for two to eight years,
(c) breaches an important duty arising from his employment, profession, position or function or imposed upon him by law, or
d) causing serious bodily harm by such an act.
(3) A sentence of imprisonment for three to ten years will be imposed on a perpetrator who causes serious injury to the health of at least two people or death by the act described in paragraph 1.
(4) The perpetrator will be sentenced to imprisonment for five to twelve years if, by the act mentioned in paragraph 1, he causes the death of at least two persons.
