In the past 24 hours, 29,929 new infections have been registered.
It's the fewest daily cases since Oct. 13.
The total number of registered infections in Russia is 10,016,896.
The daily death toll is 1,132, the lowest daily death toll since the end of October.
Britain is facing an "inevitable" large wave of Omicron infections, Dr Susan Hopkins, the chief medical adviser to the UK Health Security Agency, told television on Sunday.
New quarantine measures will be required.
People infected with Omicron are already in hospital in the UK and Hopkins expects that number to rise.
So far, no one has died from Omicron, but hospitalizations occur about 14 days after infection and deaths about three weeks after infection.
